==English==
===Etymology===
Mediæval Latin [[plenipotentiarius]], from Latin [[plenus]] ‘full’ + [[potentia]] ‘power’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /plɛnɪpə'tɛnʃəri/

===Noun===
'''plenipotentiary'''
# A person invested with [[full]] [[power]], especially as the [[agent]] or [[ambassador]] of a sovereign
#:*'''1985''': Two of them are hanging up there on Golgotha, and that ought to be enough to show the authority of Rome’s ah '''plenipotentiary'''. — Anthony Burgess, ''Kingdom of the Wicked''

===Adjective===
'''plenipotentiary'''
# invested with full power
# of, or related to a plenipotentiary


